Spicules.
Oxeas in one size class (91–155 (15)–216/ 2–7 (1.9)– 
15 µm
), smooth, slightly curved to straight, usually with acerate edges that vary to hastate and rounded (
Fig. 2G–J
) (
Table 1
).

